import json, websocket


eventIO = 20
trackname = ""
event = ""


class car(object):
    def __init__(self):
        self.startnummer = 0
        self.team = ""
        self.position = 0
        self.inClassPos = 0
        self.driver = ""
        self.raceclass = ""
        self.car = ""


    def __str__(self):
        return str(self.__class__) + ": " + str(self.__dict__)


def on_message(ws, message):
    global trackname
    global event
    json_message = json.loads(message)
    
    if trackname == "":
        trackname = json_message["TRACKNAME"]
        print(trackname)
        
    if event == "":
        event = json_message["CUP"]
        print(event)
        
    json_results = json_message["RESULT"]
    listOfcars = []
    
    for pos in json_results:
        ccar = car()
        ccar.position = pos["RANK"]
        ccar.startnummer = pos["STNR"]
        ccar.team = pos["TEAM"]
        ccar.inClassPos = pos["CLASSRANK"]
        ccar.driver = pos["NAME"]
        ccar.raceclass = pos["CLASSNAME"]
        ccar.car = pos["CAR"]
        listOfcars.append(ccar)
        print(ccar)


def on_open(ws):
    ws.send("{\"eventId\":\"" + str(eventIO) + "\", \"target\":\"results-table\"}")


ws = websocket.WebSocketApp("wss://livetiming.azurewebsites.net/ws",
                            on_message=on_message,
                            on_open=on_open)

ws.run_forever()
